---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import { site } from '../../config/site';

const crumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { name: 'Privacy', href: '/privacy/' }
];
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy | Muraqabah Initiative"
  description="How Muraqabah Initiative collects, uses, and protects your information across our website, forms, and communications."
>
  <PageHero eyebrow="Privacy" title="Privacy policy" lede="We ask for as little as possible, use it only for the reason you shared it, and never sell it." crumbs={crumbs} />

  <section class="section section--tight">
    <div class="container container--narrow prose">
      <p><em>Last updated: July 2026</em></p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <p>
        You can browse this website without providing any personal information. We collect information only when
        you choose to share it, for example when you submit a contact, volunteer, partnership, or interest form.
        Depending on the form, this may include your name, email address, phone number, city, and the message or
        details you provide.
      </p>

      <h2>How we use it</h2>
      <p>
        We use your information solely to respond to your inquiry, coordinate the activity you expressed interest
        in, and send you updates you have asked for. We do not sell, rent, or trade personal information.
      </p>

      <h2>Forms and email</h2>
      <p>
        Form submissions are delivered to {site.email} through a form delivery service. Emails you send us are
        handled through our email provider. Please avoid including sensitive personal information in form
        submissions.
      </p>

      <h2>Donations</h2>
      <p>
        Donations and program registrations are processed by Zeffy on Zeffy's own platform. Muraqabah does not
        receive or store your payment card details. Zeffy's handling of your information is governed by Zeffy's
        own privacy policy, which is available on their website.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party content</h2>
      <p>
        Some pages embed videos hosted on YouTube. We use YouTube's privacy-enhanced player, which delays
        connections to YouTube until you choose to play a video. Once you press play, YouTube's own privacy
        practices apply. Links to our social media profiles take you to platforms governed by their own policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics and cookies</h2>
      <p>
        This website does not set advertising or tracking cookies. If we enable website analytics in the future,
        we intend to use a privacy-conscious service and will update this policy accordingly.
      </p>

      <h2>Retention and your choices</h2>
      <p>
        We keep correspondence and form submissions only as long as needed to serve the purpose they were sent
        for. You may ask us at any time to correct or delete information you have shared with us, or to stop
        contacting you, by emailing <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        Our website is intended for a general audience. Program registrations for minors should be completed by
        a parent or guardian.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If our practices change, we will update this page and revise the date at the top. Questions about this
        policy can be sent to <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
